Package me.bristermitten.plumber.scheduling.timings

Interface TimeUnitPicker<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the return type (generally a parent interface)
    public interface TimeUnitPicker<T>
    A TimeUnitPicker allows developers to choose a time unit for an action. General best practice is to have the method that returns a TimeUnitPicker take a long for the amount of time, for example PPlayer#blockEvent(PlayerMoveEvent.class).undoAfter(30).seconds()
